Deal Spurs Market Probe
The exchange, which has asked for a chronology of events
leading up to the announcement, noted that it "regularly
reviews market activity" and "no inference of impropriety
should be drawn from the inquiry," a McDonnell Douglas
spokesman said.
   Congressional investigators also have indicated they are
interested in examining whether McDonnell Douglas improperly
released certain inside information about the Taiwan
Aerospace deal to particular investment firms. But McDonnell
Douglas officials countered that they "maintained total
propriety" in disclosing information on the deal.

